I've now opened for @willienelsonofficial 11 times, and the grateful feeling I get while on that stage still hasn't diminished. If you would have told 18 year old me that one day I would have the honor of opening for and singing with such a legend, I would have laughed in your face.

 I often feel like I still haven't found exactly where I fit in this industry, but having the privilege to watch Willie  perform so many times has taught something.  It has taught me that being unapologetically true to yourself and your art while carrying with you a kind and humble spirit will keep you moving in the right direction. Thank you, Willie. Until next time. 🙏🏻
